from each other we can hardly hope
to discover by generalisations the
changes infinitely more complex
produces in living beings -
Hence the first steps towards the
progress of the science of animated
Nature must depend upon the perfection
the science of inanimate nature. -
principles [unclear]undecompounded[/unclear] in their
combinations must be ascertained
Hence the changes effected in the blood
on which life depends or by which
new modes of action are generated
become the first & most important
desiderata. -

