The changes effected by living beings by
inanimate matter in short the animation
of matter are at present unknown
to chemistry, the great number of attractions
& of principles concerned in those changes
place them at present out of the
reach of our faculties. The only mode
in which we can ever hope to estimate
these changes is by ascertaining with
accuracy their composition properties

